{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e62d2e44-10e2-468e-96e0-e0aff09fc130","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** these packages:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Add** this property to your `<PropertyGroup>`:\n   ```xml\n   <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   ```\n   This ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest.\n\n4. **Optional but recommended** — enable the MTP test runner entry point:\n   ```xml\n   <GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>\n   ```\n\n5. **Run tests** with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or directly via the built executable: `./bin/Debug/net8.0/YourProject.exe`\n\nKey differences to be aware of:\n- MTP runs each test project as its own process (no shared test host).\n- CLI flags change (e.g., `--filter` becomes `--filter` on MTP too, but some VSTest-specific flags won't work).\n- If you use `runsettings`, you may need to adjust — MTP uses its own configuration model.\n\nWould you like me to make these changes to your project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bcb5d55a-b8d0-4d77-af75-17eb27b6db7f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using `xunit.runner.visualstudio`) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":422},"id":"f2b8ca37-81b7-4a53-964f-77cb480b97bc","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:04:41.537Z","parentId":"52ed31a7-69f7-42a1-bad7-73f85b0b69b3"}
